{"source_key":"sha256-ed44dfead10cc60ed1f264086c388e5c","record_index":1557,"record_hash":"sha256:4604db0703610d6d568aa37bac09726b54532011693a1f371b73c9508c3f69c0","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:04.841Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- **P2: `max_sessions` caps too late.** [gitmeta.rs:382](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:382) builds every `SessionSummary`, and [gitmeta.rs:469](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:469) parses every turn for every session before `truncate`. That makes `Some(1)` still O(all sessions * all turns), and one malformed old session can make “latest 1” fail. Sort/cap on lightweight metadata first, then hydrate returned sessions. Also compute `turn_count` from list length and parse only the last turn for `latest_turn_key`.\\n\\n- **P2: `updated_at` sorting is raw string sorting.** [gitmeta.rs:386](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:386) only works because writers currently emit fixed UTC millis. A malformed or offset timestamp silently sorts wrong. Parse with `DateTime::parse_from_rfc3339` for the internal sort key, bail on malformed existing values, and keep the public `String` if that’s the API shape.\\n\\n- **P3: missing per-session keys are treated as valid empty data.** [gitmeta.rs:452](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:452), [gitmeta.rs:460](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:460), and [gitmeta.rs:587](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:587) let an indexed session with missing `updated-at`, `sources`, or `turns` appear as a real empty summary. I’d make indexed-session core keys required, or explicitly skip orphaned sessions with a comment. Silent fake summaries are maintenance debt.\\n\\nNo visibility/cloning issues worth calling out in [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:12); the re-export is fine. I didn’t edit files or run tests.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:19:04.841Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}